<paragraph id="3A4B58729322FFB5CDD687F9FE98FA9E" blockId="13.[151,636,1231,1291]" box="[151,337,1266,1291]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">
(
<figureCitation id="A2CF44F79322FFB5CDDE87F9FEE9FA9E" box="[159,288,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 42" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1754]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 42. Species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD 23 – 24. A. praestigiosa. 25 – 26. A. johannismarci. 27 – 28. A. brevignoni sp. nov. holotype. 29 – 30. A. rameli. 31 – 34. A. willmotti sp. nov.. 31 – 32. Male holotye. 33 – 34. Female allotype. 35 – 38. A. iracyi. 35 – 36. Male. 37 – 38. Female. 39 – 42. A. saulensis tunari comb. nov. 39 – 40. Male. 41 – 42. Female. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233290/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">
Figs 
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5CD9687F8FEE9FA9E" box="[215,288,1267,1291]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="29.795" valueMax="30.59" valueMin="29.0">29–30</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A2CF44F79322FFB5CC6A87F9FE81FA9E" box="[299,328,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 56 – 62" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1346,1368]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,267,1324]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,267,1324]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 56 – 62. Male genitalia of species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 56. A. praestigiosa. 57. A. johannismarci. 58. A. brevignoni sp. nov. holotype. 59. A. rameli. 60. A. willmotti sp. nov. holotype. 61. A. iracyi. 62. A. saulensis tunari comb. nov. Left to right: dorsal view of uncus, lateral view of tegumen, saccus, uncus, gnathos, valva and aedeagus, and ventral view of valva. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233293/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">59</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A4B58729322FFB5CDD68631FC36F902" blockId="13.[151,1437,1338,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">
This is the most common 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F19322FFB5CCF98630FDB7FAC7" box="[440,638,1339,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="088084609322FFB5CCF98630FDB7FAC7" box="[440,638,1339,1362]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">Argyrogrammana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species found at the 
<collectionCode id="5CE5C0B79322FFB5CE288630FC7AFAC6" box="[873,947,1339,1363]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">PNSD</collectionCode>
, with 
<specimenCount id="2CF293FB9322FFB5CEB78630FB93FAC6" box="[1014,1114,1338,1363]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" type="male">
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5CEB78630FBDBFAC6" box="[1014,1042,1339,1363]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="13.0">13</number>
males
</specimenCount>
specimens collected in 
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5C8248630FA55FAC6" box="[1381,1436,1339,1363]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="2011.0">2011</number>
(four), 
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5CDA98654FEE9FAE2" box="[232,288,1375,1399]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="2013.0">2013</number>
(four) and 
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5CCE28654FE12FAE2" box="[419,475,1375,1399]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="2014.0">2014</number>
(five). Specimens were seen in different days at the hilltop, flying about one to two meters above the ground, at 
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5CC908689FE24FA0E" box="[465,493,1410,1435]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="14.0">14</number>
:00– 
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5CF608689FDF4FA0E" box="[545,573,1410,1435]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="16.0">16</number>
:00h. Some males fought in circular flight, after resting on underside’s leaves. The specimens recorded at the 
<collectionCode id="5CE5C0B79322FFB5CCB886ACFD89FA2A" box="[505,576,1447,1471]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">PNSD</collectionCode>
differ in some features from that one illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="5E6525839322FFB5C9CE86ADFA55FA2A" author="Hall" box="[1167,1436,1446,1471]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1996) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, part 2, with one new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 7, 71 - 80." type="journal article" year="1996">
Hall &amp; Willmott (
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5C81B86ADFA5DFA2A" box="[1370,1428,1446,1471]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
from Tefé, Amazonas, 
<collectingCountry id="42E318E29322FFB5CCE186C1FE2DFA76" box="[416,484,1482,1507]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="42E318E29322FFB5CF6186C1FDB6FA76" box="[544,639,1482,1507]" name="Ecuador" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and by 
<bibRefCitation id="5E6525839322FFB5CFA486C1FBE4FA76" author="Brevignon" box="[741,1069,1482,1507]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard (
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5CEAA86C1FBECFA76" box="[1003,1061,1482,1507]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry id="42E318E29322FFB5C93686C1FAEAFA76" box="[1143,1315,1482,1507]" name="French Guiana" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
. The most notable differences are the larger yellow bands, and the presence of an orange band from the outer margin to the silvery blue submarginal band in both wings. Even though, the male genitalia only differ slightly from the illustrations provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="5E6525839322FFB5CC81853DFCC6F9DA" author="Brevignon" box="[448,783,1590,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard (
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5CF8C853DFCCEF9DA" box="[717,775,1590,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="5E6525839322FFB5CE10853DFBA4F9DA" author="Hall" box="[849,1133,1590,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1996) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, part 2, with one new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 7, 71 - 80." type="journal article" year="1996">
Hall &amp; Willmott (
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5C969853DFBACF9DA" box="[1064,1125,1590,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Following the schematic drawings for identification of sibling species belonging to the “ 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F19322FFB5CE348551FC1DF9E6" box="[885,980,1626,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trochilia">
<emphasis id="088084609322FFB5CE348551FC1DF9E6" box="[885,980,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">trochilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex” (
<bibRefCitation id="5E6525839322FFB5C91C8551FA47F9E6" author="Hall" box="[1117,1422,1626,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1996) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, part 2, with one new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 7, 71 - 80." type="journal article" year="1996">
Hall &amp; Willmott 
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5C8678551FAABF9E6" box="[1318,1378,1626,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="1996.0">1996</number>
: 
<number id="8C3C4A559322FFB5C82E8550FA47F9E6" box="[1391,1422,1627,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240" value="77.0">77</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), there is little doubt about the identity of the specimens collected at the 
<collectionCode id="5CE5C0B79322FFB5CEEE8574FC33F902" box="[943,1018,1663,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="240">PNSD</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
